01:21.349 --> 01:26.454
* The carolers are singing *

01:26.520 --> 01:31.959
* And this I know, my dear *

01:32.025 --> 01:35.163
* Next Christmas *

01:35.229 --> 01:37.665
-(applause)
-* Is this Christmas... *

01:37.731 --> 01:39.867
BRADY:
Great work, everyone.

01:39.933 --> 01:43.837
* And this Christmas *

01:43.904 --> 01:45.839
* Is here. *

01:48.842 --> 01:51.445
BRADY (voice-over):
Looks like we got a hit!

01:51.512 --> 01:54.615
Sell enough tickets
to choke the MGM lion.

01:54.682 --> 01:55.883
Ho, ho, ho.

01:55.949 --> 01:57.918
What would you like
for Christmas, little girl?

01:57.985 --> 02:00.554
You are my Christmas present.

02:00.621 --> 02:01.389
(laughs)

02:01.455 --> 02:02.890
When are you gonna unwrap me?

02:02.956 --> 02:04.492
Wasn't that the sweetest story
you ever saw?

02:04.558 --> 02:06.059
No more candy canes,
you had two already.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.895
I'll get you some popcorn,
come on.

02:07.961 --> 02:09.163
HACKETT:
Hey, boss.

02:09.229 --> 02:10.764
Here's to Christmas miracles.

02:10.830 --> 02:12.466
Yeah. Merry Christmas.

02:12.533 --> 02:15.002
-That whole confession bit.
-Uh-uh.

02:15.068 --> 02:16.804
-Was that...?
-Stahr's idea.

02:16.870 --> 02:19.707
-But Kay's words. -Now, now,
we'll have none of that here.

02:19.773 --> 02:23.811
To Monroe Stahr, who,
in a mad reign of terror,

02:23.877 --> 02:25.946
fired his editor, producer,
director and--

02:26.013 --> 02:28.582
God forgive us-- his writer,

02:28.649 --> 02:30.984
not to mention his boozehound
leading man,

02:31.051 --> 02:34.588
the scenery-chewing,
ingÃƒÂ©nue-screwing Mr. Frost,

02:34.655 --> 02:37.391
and turned tragedy to a triumph.

02:37.458 --> 02:39.593
-Hear, hear. -Cheers.
-Hear, hear.

02:39.660 --> 02:41.262
It was Pat's baby,
start to finish.

02:41.329 --> 02:44.131
What do you think of it, Hannah?

02:44.198 --> 02:46.600
Um...

02:46.667 --> 02:48.369
I don't know.

02:48.436 --> 02:51.104
It is my first
American Christmas.

02:51.171 --> 02:52.440
Is that really
what they are like?

02:52.506 --> 02:54.442
-Yes. -STAHR: More or less.
-Yes, yes, yes.

02:54.508 --> 02:55.709
Perfectly accurate.

02:55.776 --> 02:57.945
How'd they like it?

02:58.011 --> 02:59.647
I don't think Nathan's
ever gonna be the same.

02:59.713 --> 03:01.482
I mean, not too long ago,
movie theaters

03:01.549 --> 03:04.485
were something we looked for
to get out of the rain.

03:04.552 --> 03:06.153
I'm letting them see it
again this afternoon,

03:06.220 --> 03:07.755
just the two of them,
at the Egyptian.

03:07.821 --> 03:09.990
It's what they wanted
for Christmas.

03:10.057 --> 03:11.459
Hear that, Daddy?

03:11.525 --> 03:14.295
-Paying customers.
-(grunts)

03:14.362 --> 03:16.897
(quietly):
Excuse me.

03:16.964 --> 03:19.600
Well, if it isn't the Jew
who invented Christmas.

03:19.667 --> 03:21.735
I think another Jew gets credit
for that one.

03:21.802 --> 03:23.471
BRADY:
Tell that to your disciples.

03:23.537 --> 03:24.905
STAHR: Be happy, Pat.
Your movie works.

03:24.972 --> 03:27.308
BRADY: They're my employees,
they have to like it.

03:27.375 --> 03:28.442
STAHR:
But I don't.

03:28.509 --> 03:30.444
And I'm telling you, it's a hit.

03:30.511 --> 03:32.946
Excuse me.
Hate to interrupt. Um...

03:33.013 --> 03:35.716
We should really go, if we're
gonna get there before dark.

03:35.783 --> 03:37.551
Swell.
You grab all the applause,

03:37.618 --> 03:39.253
I got to worry
about the box office.

03:39.320 --> 03:40.988
They have got phones in Big
Bear, Pat. I'll be checking in.

03:41.054 --> 03:43.223
But will you be dying inside,
sweating out every call

03:43.291 --> 03:45.393
-from distribution?
-Dying, dying.

03:45.459 --> 03:47.961
Aching, I promise.

03:51.399 --> 03:54.234
The hell's he doing here?

03:55.503 --> 03:57.438
STAHR:
Shall I call security, Vajna?

03:57.505 --> 03:58.872
Take it easy, Monroe.

03:58.939 --> 04:00.974
It's bad luck
to treat old friends like that.

04:01.041 --> 04:02.242
STAHR:
Old friends.

04:02.310 --> 04:03.444
And you got a hit on your hands.

04:03.511 --> 04:05.646
Say, I hear, uh,
you got an unknown

04:05.713 --> 04:07.281
starring in your next picture.

04:07.348 --> 04:09.249
She seeking representation?

04:09.317 --> 04:10.584
(scoffs)

04:10.651 --> 04:12.820
I'd sooner put her with Hitler.

04:12.886 --> 04:14.388
You must know that.

04:14.455 --> 04:16.290
That's what I don't get
about you, Stahr.

04:16.357 --> 04:19.392
You can turn even a simple chat
into high drama.

04:19.459 --> 04:21.028
That what this is?

04:21.094 --> 04:22.463
A simple chat?

04:22.530 --> 04:25.466
How about you get off my lot?

04:25.533 --> 04:27.668
I was just leaving.

04:29.202 --> 04:31.104
(talking quietly)

04:31.171 --> 04:32.806
-We'll see you next week.
-KAY: Have a wonderful time.

04:32.873 --> 04:34.408
-Have a great weekend.
-HACKETT: Have fun.

04:34.475 --> 04:36.009
-Bye-bye.
-STAHR: Congratulations.

04:43.083 --> 04:44.184
(sighs)

04:44.251 --> 04:45.753
What about Otis?

04:45.819 --> 04:47.054
For our snowman.

04:47.120 --> 04:48.255
Otis?

04:48.322 --> 04:50.190
Get him a fine cashmere scarf,

04:50.257 --> 04:51.559
a calabash pipe,

04:51.625 --> 04:54.928
make him a real gentleman.

04:54.995 --> 04:57.598
Well-read, charming,

04:57.665 --> 05:00.634
a wise observer of humanity.

05:00.701 --> 05:03.203
Oh, and a whiskey drinker.

05:03.270 --> 05:04.372
Mm.

05:04.438 --> 05:06.540
Should I be jealous?

05:06.607 --> 05:09.109
Oh, it depends
if you got me a present.

05:09.176 --> 05:10.411
I can't tell you.

05:10.478 --> 05:12.446
-Not till tomorrow.
-Really?

05:12.513 --> 05:14.715
LANG:
Mr. Stahr.

05:14.782 --> 05:15.616
My compliments.

05:15.683 --> 05:17.651
That was quite something.

05:17.718 --> 05:20.854
I have never seen a film
dipped in sugar before.

05:20.921 --> 05:23.357
Glad I cut the dancing
gingerbread number,

05:23.424 --> 05:25.192
-you would've hated that.
-Hmm.

05:25.258 --> 05:27.595
Is this the kind of movie
you expect me to make,

05:27.661 --> 05:28.829
a picture book for children?

05:28.896 --> 05:31.399
You make the film you want,
Fritz.

05:31.465 --> 05:32.633
That's why I hired you.

05:32.700 --> 05:34.902
Yes, but how
should I make anything

05:34.968 --> 05:37.371
with an actress
who refuses to rehearse?

05:39.239 --> 05:40.340
Mr. Lang...

05:40.408 --> 05:42.009
Six weeks.

05:42.075 --> 05:44.077
Six weeks to prepare.

05:44.144 --> 05:45.979
And this one refuses me.

05:46.046 --> 05:48.482
-I don't understand.
-LANG: You didn't tell him?

05:48.549 --> 05:52.019
He wanted to rehearse
this weekend.

05:52.085 --> 05:55.155
LANG: 24 hours
of uninterrupted rehearsals.

05:55.222 --> 05:58.559
An acquaintance lent me
his home for the purpose.

05:58.626 --> 06:02.029
Axel here left his family
in the middle of a trip.

06:02.095 --> 06:03.964
But my leading actress,

06:04.031 --> 06:08.469
who has uttered a total
of zero words on film, declined.

06:08.536 --> 06:10.438
(exhales)

06:10.504 --> 06:11.905
You and I had plans.

06:11.972 --> 06:13.907
We were looking forward
to going.

06:13.974 --> 06:17.277
Due to the insane schedule
you have put me on, Monroe,

06:17.344 --> 06:19.447
this is the only time
I will have free

06:19.513 --> 06:21.782
between now and the day we wrap.

06:21.849 --> 06:23.517
I thought, perhaps,
Miss Garbo here

06:23.584 --> 06:25.719
might make an accommodation.

06:25.786 --> 06:28.021
(scoffs)

06:29.890 --> 06:31.559
Monroe.

06:31.625 --> 06:32.993
I'm sorry, darling.

06:33.060 --> 06:34.528
He's the director.

06:34.595 --> 06:36.897
LANG:
At last, an adult decides.

06:36.964 --> 06:39.567
Thank you, Mr. Stahr.
Please, Axel, take her luggage.

06:39.633 --> 06:40.768
(clears throat)

06:40.834 --> 06:44.337
(quietly):
Is it, uh...

06:44.404 --> 06:46.073
Just, uh...

06:46.139 --> 06:47.608
Uh.

06:48.842 --> 06:49.943
(exhales)

06:50.010 --> 06:51.712
(door closes)

06:57.317 --> 06:58.819
How could you do this?

06:58.886 --> 07:00.353
There'll be other weekends.

07:00.420 --> 07:01.755
It's Christmas Eve.

07:01.822 --> 07:04.191
It's a chance
to make the movie better

07:04.257 --> 07:06.760
and rehearse with one of
the world's greatest directors.

07:06.827 --> 07:08.929
You have to, for your career.

07:08.996 --> 07:10.864
My career.

07:10.931 --> 07:12.399
Exactly.

07:12.466 --> 07:14.401
You had no right
to speak for me.

07:14.468 --> 07:16.737
I was speaking for the picture.

07:16.804 --> 07:18.706
Good to know your priorities.

07:18.772 --> 07:20.874
Kathleen, that is not fair.

07:20.941 --> 07:23.243
This is important, you and I.

07:23.310 --> 07:26.279
I mean, if...
if we don't matter to you...

07:26.346 --> 07:29.149
At Christmas, in my family,

07:29.216 --> 07:32.085
-we would never...
-What, do your job?

07:35.823 --> 07:39.827
We would never be away
from the people we love.

07:48.135 --> 07:49.603
Your gift.

07:55.275 --> 07:57.745
Kathleen.

08:01.682 --> 08:03.116
BRADY (voice-over):
Eh, forget Rochester.

08:03.183 --> 08:05.352
That town's a toilet bowl.
What about Stamford?

08:05.418 --> 08:08.221
Must be gangbusters in Stamford.

08:08.288 --> 08:11.458
Goddamn matinees.

08:11.525 --> 08:13.160
Call me with an update later.

08:13.226 --> 08:14.494
Yeah.

08:14.562 --> 08:16.664
Merry Christmas to you, too.

08:16.730 --> 08:18.498
(slams phone)

08:20.300 --> 08:22.502
(groans)

08:22.570 --> 08:24.705
Nobody's coming out.

08:24.772 --> 08:27.507
Not even the hayseeds.

08:27.575 --> 08:29.743
I don't understand it.

08:29.810 --> 08:32.412
We spent a fortune
marketing this thing.

08:32.479 --> 08:34.715
Can I get you anything,
Mr. Brady?

08:34.782 --> 08:36.216
Ads in all the major newspapers.

08:36.283 --> 08:38.251
Billboards, posters,
you can't even take a piss

08:38.318 --> 08:41.554
without Leslie Reeves
grinning back at you.

08:41.621 --> 08:45.092
It's just the first matinee,
sir.

08:45.158 --> 08:46.660
It'll pick up.

08:48.028 --> 08:50.463
My sister in Evanston's
taking her family tonight.

08:50.530 --> 08:51.565
How many kids she got?

08:51.632 --> 08:53.767
Just my niece.

08:53.834 --> 08:55.603
You couldn't
have been Catholic, Birdy?

08:55.669 --> 08:57.938
(laughs softly)

08:59.907 --> 09:04.912
Go home and be with your family,
Mr. Brady.

09:04.978 --> 09:06.313
Yeah.

09:06.379 --> 09:08.682
You, too.

09:12.853 --> 09:15.122
Could I have some water?

09:15.188 --> 09:19.192
No, sweetie, I'm sorry,
you can't.

09:21.094 --> 09:23.496
The doctor was in
a little bit ago,

09:23.563 --> 09:25.899
and I don't want you to worry,

09:25.966 --> 09:28.869
they need to operate.

09:28.936 --> 09:30.904
They think there might be
a bleed in there.

09:30.971 --> 09:34.374
So they are gonna go in
and fix it right up.

09:34.441 --> 09:36.576
(exhales)

09:44.117 --> 09:46.153
Mr. Brady?

09:46.219 --> 09:48.555
Yes, Miner. What is it?

09:48.622 --> 09:50.858
(laughs softly)

09:50.924 --> 09:54.061
Mr. Stahr wants a revised budget
on his desk by Monday,

09:54.127 --> 09:57.597
so it's holiday
be damned for me.

09:57.665 --> 09:59.166
Okay.

09:59.232 --> 10:02.736
Well, I'm sorry to interrupt,
ma'am.

10:02.803 --> 10:05.238
Whatcha got there?

10:05.305 --> 10:08.108
Just, uh... some goodies.

10:08.175 --> 10:10.010
Hmm.

10:12.112 --> 10:13.246
Want some?

10:13.313 --> 10:16.684
I better not,
I'm still on the clock.

10:16.750 --> 10:19.086
Why don't you--

10:19.152 --> 10:21.388
if Nathan and Darla
are off at the movies--

10:21.454 --> 10:23.323
come over for dinner?

10:23.390 --> 10:25.358
Come, come over.

10:25.425 --> 10:27.294
To the mansion.

10:27.360 --> 10:29.062
You had me over last time.

10:29.129 --> 10:31.999
Well, that's not the same thing
as the Okie coming over

10:32.065 --> 10:34.634
to Mr. Brady's on Christmas Eve.

10:36.536 --> 10:38.205
Maybe...

10:38.271 --> 10:41.909
maybe, if, if I didn't have
just this one suit.

10:41.975 --> 10:44.244
It's hardly Buckingham Palace,
Max.

10:45.979 --> 10:47.915
Let me tell you how it would go.

10:47.981 --> 10:49.516
I'd meet you at the door.

10:49.582 --> 10:51.018
No butler?

10:51.084 --> 10:52.152
Night off.

10:52.219 --> 10:54.187
I'd have a hot cider
waiting for you.

10:54.254 --> 10:56.990
And then we'd go into the parlor
for some tree trimming.

10:57.057 --> 10:59.592
(exhales)
Me and the boss.

10:59.659 --> 11:02.495
No. Daddy would be on the phone.

11:02.562 --> 11:04.364
He's always on the phone.

11:04.431 --> 11:07.367
But my mother will love you.

11:07.434 --> 11:10.003
She already thinks
you're very charming.

11:11.071 --> 11:12.806
Those Brady women are clever.

11:12.873 --> 11:16.810
We'd have a drink on the patio.

11:16.877 --> 11:19.179
It's cold out.

11:19.246 --> 11:22.415
Could put my jacket
over your shoulders.

11:22.482 --> 11:23.683
Winning more points with mother.

11:23.751 --> 11:25.118
Good.

11:25.185 --> 11:28.822
We'd look up at the stars...

11:31.691 --> 11:32.525
(popcorn drops)

11:32.592 --> 11:34.294
-Max, I wasn't...
-I'm sorry, was that bad?

11:34.361 --> 11:36.496
Well, I-I thought
we were pretending.

11:36.563 --> 11:38.398
-I don't know, were we?
I'm sorry. -I don't know.

11:38.465 --> 11:40.433
-I'm sorry, here you go.
-Wait, but I didn't...

11:40.500 --> 11:42.803
-mean to... -I-I don't know,
you were coming towards me, I...

11:42.870 --> 11:45.472
I-I'm sorry.
And I mess up.

12:06.827 --> 12:09.662
AXEL:
Now, whose house is this, Fritz?

12:09.729 --> 12:11.899
A nothing manager
trying to sign me.

12:11.965 --> 12:13.934
(speaks in German)

12:14.001 --> 12:16.870
I needed the space,
so I am allowing him to believe

12:16.937 --> 12:18.638
I take him seriously.

12:18.705 --> 12:21.174
Don't eat the props, Axel.

12:24.677 --> 12:26.613
(knocking on door)

12:26.679 --> 12:28.481
(door creaks open)

12:28.548 --> 12:30.818
Clint.

12:30.884 --> 12:33.386
Merry Christmas, Monroe.

12:33.453 --> 12:36.023
Uh...
(chuckles)

12:36.089 --> 12:37.991
Wasn't expecting you.

12:38.058 --> 12:40.227
You saved it, pal.

12:40.293 --> 12:44.031
"Angels on the Avenue,"
it's... it's wonderful.

12:44.097 --> 12:45.432
Leslie was wonderful.

12:45.498 --> 12:49.636
This is the Christmas
America dreams about.

12:49.702 --> 12:54.574
I just wanted to say
congratulations, and thank you.

12:54.641 --> 12:56.409
Uh...

12:56.476 --> 12:58.311
You'll have to forgive me,
Clint.

12:58.378 --> 13:01.915
People don't often respond
to being fired so graciously.

13:01.982 --> 13:05.618
No, well, I wasn't gracious
that first week.

13:05.685 --> 13:09.789
I drank up just about everything
but the L.A. River.

13:09.857 --> 13:11.959
But then I ran
into Burt Ainsley.

13:12.025 --> 13:13.326
Remember him?

13:13.393 --> 13:16.463
Yeah, sure.
From the silent days.

13:20.633 --> 13:23.103
Please. Have a seat.

13:23.170 --> 13:25.973
Well, he took me in,

13:26.039 --> 13:29.142
dried me out, showed me
what I was doing to myself.

13:29.209 --> 13:31.411
Even found me an acting coach.

13:31.478 --> 13:33.513
So, thank you.

13:33.580 --> 13:35.715
You saved me.

13:35.782 --> 13:37.217
I'm happy to hear that.

13:37.284 --> 13:39.452
Well, Burt's having a party
tonight.

13:39.519 --> 13:41.354
Real holiday shindig.

13:41.421 --> 13:42.822
You should come.

13:42.890 --> 13:44.024
Ah, I don't know.

13:44.091 --> 13:45.959
Uh, there's so much
to catch up on.

13:46.026 --> 13:48.428
Come on, it's Christmas.

14:01.909 --> 14:03.243
See you tonight.

14:07.547 --> 14:08.916
Oh, and, uh...

14:08.982 --> 14:11.151
bring that pretty girl of yours.

14:11.218 --> 14:13.353
(door opens, then closes)

14:21.794 --> 14:24.697
So, let me understand,

14:24.764 --> 14:26.900
you can't have dinner,

14:26.967 --> 14:29.169
you can't have a drink,

14:29.236 --> 14:33.873
you can't go for a walk
because you have an appointment.

14:33.941 --> 14:36.576
-On Christmas Eve.
-Yeah.

14:36.643 --> 14:37.877
I know it sounds...

14:37.945 --> 14:39.612
Curious?

14:43.350 --> 14:44.484
(sighs)

14:44.551 --> 14:46.119
It's stupid, it's, um...

14:46.186 --> 14:47.988
it's Mass,
it's Christmas Eve Mass.

14:48.055 --> 14:50.157
-I only go once a year and...
-(gasps)

14:50.223 --> 14:53.026
That is disgraceful.

14:53.093 --> 14:54.794
At home,
we call that a "shonde."

14:54.861 --> 14:56.129
Shameful.

14:56.196 --> 14:58.131
What, do you take Communion?

14:58.198 --> 15:01.534
You light a prayer candle?

15:01.601 --> 15:03.971
No.

15:04.037 --> 15:05.939
It's worse than that.

15:11.611 --> 15:13.046
I sing in the choir.

15:13.113 --> 15:15.048
-You do?
-Baritone.

15:17.150 --> 15:20.353
I love Christmas Eve Mass.

15:20.420 --> 15:21.554
I want to come.

15:21.621 --> 15:23.690
-No.
-Please.

15:23.756 --> 15:25.658
No, I'm not a performer, I...

15:25.725 --> 15:27.127
I'm not really even a singer.

15:28.728 --> 15:30.998
Please.

15:33.033 --> 15:34.601
All right.

15:34.667 --> 15:37.304
On one condition:

15:37.370 --> 15:42.875
you tell no one what you saw.

15:42.942 --> 15:44.377
Do you swear?

15:45.645 --> 15:47.047
So help me God.

15:47.114 --> 15:49.182
(organ music, children laughing)

15:49.249 --> 15:51.051
PRIEST:
Bobby, Tommy, no running, boys.

15:51.118 --> 15:53.286
-BOY: Yes, Father.
-That's it.

15:56.089 --> 15:57.424
(Brady moans)

15:59.659 --> 16:01.128
(moans loudly)

16:04.931 --> 16:07.067
May I help you, my son?

16:07.134 --> 16:08.668
You seem in distress.

16:08.735 --> 16:10.837
Sorry, Father, I...

16:10.903 --> 16:12.239
I...

16:15.108 --> 16:17.544
Perhaps we can sit in silence.

16:19.012 --> 16:20.347
No, no, I...

16:20.413 --> 16:23.750
I brought a baby into the world.

16:23.816 --> 16:27.487
Beautiful baby.

16:27.554 --> 16:29.789
Was it great.

16:29.856 --> 16:31.624
Pride, joy...

16:32.859 --> 16:35.095
...anticipation.

16:35.162 --> 16:37.264
So full of promise.

16:37.330 --> 16:41.000
But, Father,
my baby has taken a turn.

16:41.068 --> 16:46.005
My baby is... in crisis.

16:46.073 --> 16:47.507
And I'm scared.

16:47.574 --> 16:49.276
Hmm.

16:49.342 --> 16:51.411
Stuck, waiting for news.

16:51.478 --> 16:53.146
It might not survive
the weekend.

16:54.447 --> 16:56.383
(sighs)

16:58.418 --> 17:01.788
I am so sorry
for your suffering, my son.

17:01.854 --> 17:03.190
Can I help?

17:04.257 --> 17:05.458
I do need your help, Father.

17:05.525 --> 17:06.925
From your whole congregation.

17:06.992 --> 17:09.662
Well, we will pray
for the little one, of course.

17:09.729 --> 17:11.030
Prayer may not be enough.

17:11.098 --> 17:13.700
Prayer is always enough.

17:20.207 --> 17:22.942
That... is a multitude
of tickets

17:23.009 --> 17:25.212
to the new Brady-American
picture,

17:25.278 --> 17:28.248
"Angels on the Avenue."

17:28.315 --> 17:30.717
I need you to distribute them.

17:33.720 --> 17:35.188
Tickets?

17:35.255 --> 17:39.025
One per family.

17:39.092 --> 17:41.294
If you would.

17:41.361 --> 17:44.831
Do you believe in confession?

17:44.897 --> 17:47.267
Well, I'm not Catholic.

17:47.334 --> 17:51.037
I almost gave it a try once
on a trip to Italy.

17:51.104 --> 17:53.340
But the impulse passed.

17:53.406 --> 17:57.277
I need to say something.

17:58.511 --> 18:00.880
I wouldn't want
to take this with me.

18:00.947 --> 18:03.316
All right.

18:03.383 --> 18:06.853
I haven't been completely
honest with you,

18:06.919 --> 18:08.988
or anybody here.

18:09.055 --> 18:10.457
Okay.

18:13.360 --> 18:17.830
That theater I passed out in,

18:17.897 --> 18:21.134
I wasn't just there
to watch a picture.

18:23.236 --> 18:25.238
I don't understand.

18:26.306 --> 18:28.475
I bring men there.

18:28.541 --> 18:31.444
-Customers.
-Oh.

18:31.511 --> 18:32.679
I see.

18:32.745 --> 18:35.282
Everything else I told you
was true, I-I swear it.

18:35.348 --> 18:39.419
I just... thought
that they'd kick me out

18:39.486 --> 18:41.721
if they knew that part.

18:43.623 --> 18:47.660
And I thought you wouldn't
come see me anymore.

18:47.727 --> 18:49.296
If you want to leave,
I understand.

18:49.362 --> 18:51.231
Nobody needs to spend
Christmas Eve...

18:51.298 --> 18:55.101
I had an affair
with my husband's partner.

18:55.168 --> 18:58.271
Milton, that's his name.

19:01.441 --> 19:05.778
Handsome as the devil.

19:05.845 --> 19:08.815
It went on for two years.

19:08.881 --> 19:10.583
Two years.

19:10.650 --> 19:12.952
Yeah.

19:13.019 --> 19:16.589
I thought about it every second.

19:19.392 --> 19:23.230
So it just kept happening.

19:23.296 --> 19:25.732
He had one rule,

19:25.798 --> 19:29.001
and that was no contact
of any kind.

19:29.068 --> 19:31.304
You know, no secret notes.

19:31.371 --> 19:33.273
Of course, no phone calls.

19:34.173 --> 19:36.576
So you know how we communicated?

19:36.643 --> 19:38.278
Hmm.

19:38.345 --> 19:40.280
My husband is color-blind.

19:40.347 --> 19:44.351
I pick out his clothes for him
every day,

19:44.417 --> 19:47.454
and when I put him

19:47.520 --> 19:52.959
in this one bright red tie...

19:55.328 --> 19:59.065
...that's my signal to Milton

19:59.131 --> 20:02.435
that I'm coming over.

20:03.503 --> 20:06.606
I wasn't just cheating
on my husband...

20:08.875 --> 20:11.844
...I was making him
the messenger.

20:11.911 --> 20:13.546
(exhales)

20:16.683 --> 20:22.455
It could've destroyed
their... business,

20:22.522 --> 20:25.325
their friendship.

20:25.392 --> 20:28.261
My family.

20:28.328 --> 20:31.898
And I didn't care.

20:34.033 --> 20:36.736
It was mine.

20:38.838 --> 20:41.608
And I would do it again.

20:41.674 --> 20:45.412
Do you think that anything
you did in that theater

20:45.478 --> 20:49.282
was worse than that?

20:52.151 --> 20:54.621
It's Christmas.

21:00.192 --> 21:04.063
What do you say...

21:04.130 --> 21:06.699
we forgive ourselves?

21:15.875 --> 21:18.110
CELIA:
Mother?

21:18.177 --> 21:21.348
-Remember these?
-Mm.

21:21.414 --> 21:24.317
Do you have
a New Year's resolution?

21:24.384 --> 21:25.985
A week early for that,
isn't it?

21:26.052 --> 21:27.520
Hmm.

21:27.587 --> 21:28.921
Well, it's a big decision,

21:28.988 --> 21:31.591
to dedicate a year of your life
to something.

21:31.658 --> 21:33.793
I just wondered
if you had one yet.

21:37.697 --> 21:42.068
Oh, no, we have to use those.

21:42.134 --> 21:45.372
These were your favorite
when you were little.

21:45.438 --> 21:48.808
You used to call them
your "wee woodens."

21:48.875 --> 21:52.011
And you would make up stories
and act them out,

21:52.078 --> 21:54.814
and tell Daddy and me
not to listen.

21:54.881 --> 21:58.317
But we always did,
because they were so good.

21:58.385 --> 22:01.788
Oh, the romances.

22:01.854 --> 22:03.490
The heartbreaks.

22:06.893 --> 22:11.731
You had such an imagination
for a little girl.

22:11.798 --> 22:15.067
We're only doing silver and gold
this year.

22:22.008 --> 22:26.278
You know,
I do have a resolution.

22:26.345 --> 22:30.316
I think this is the year I stop
thinking about Monroe Stahr.

22:30.383 --> 22:33.686
-How about you?
-(door opens)

22:33.753 --> 22:36.155
I...

22:36.222 --> 22:39.792
-(door closes)
-think that's a wonderful plan.

22:42.995 --> 22:44.664
What do you think?

22:44.731 --> 22:47.700
I think I have a beautiful wife,

22:47.767 --> 22:50.903
and a beautiful daughter,

22:50.970 --> 22:54.974
and if I had a brain in my head,
I'd never leave this room,

22:55.041 --> 22:57.109
ever again.

22:57.176 --> 23:00.813
Tree's nice, too.

23:04.050 --> 23:06.953
("Silent Night" playing)

23:27.306 --> 23:29.442
* *

23:51.864 --> 23:54.166
AXEL (voice-over):
In this city of strangers,

23:54.233 --> 23:56.569
it's nice to take the time
to meet your neighbors.

23:56.636 --> 23:58.404
Don't you think?

23:58.471 --> 24:02.074
We should've done this ages ago.

24:02.141 --> 24:04.644
LANG:
Stop.

24:09.248 --> 24:13.886
You believe this man
to be a fascist spy. Ja?

24:16.022 --> 24:18.591
And here you are, alone,
in his living room,

24:18.658 --> 24:21.494
vulnerable, terrified.

24:21.561 --> 24:23.930
That's a wonderful note, Fritz.

24:29.135 --> 24:32.104
This funny, Kathleen?

24:34.173 --> 24:36.342
Begin again.

24:36.408 --> 24:39.011
(clears throat)

24:42.248 --> 24:44.383
We should've done this ages ago.

24:44.450 --> 24:47.253
No, no, no. God's sakes.

24:47.319 --> 24:51.223
That was the most
dishonest performance

24:51.290 --> 24:52.959
I have ever seen.

24:54.026 --> 24:57.096
Even the way you eat is a lie.

24:58.497 --> 25:01.233
Do it again! Eat.

25:07.106 --> 25:11.077
No, Kathleen,
I did not believe you.

25:11.143 --> 25:12.679
Excuse me.

25:19.185 --> 25:21.253
Again.

25:25.658 --> 25:26.859
Again.

25:26.926 --> 25:28.828
-Fritz, I...
-Again.

25:28.895 --> 25:30.897
Again.

25:34.133 --> 25:37.737
No wonder you were afraid
to rehearse.

25:39.005 --> 25:40.306
Again.

25:40.372 --> 25:42.575
Again, again, again!

25:44.744 --> 25:47.546
Is it so difficult?

25:48.615 --> 25:50.817
You take one peanut...

25:50.883 --> 25:54.286
and you put it in your mouth
and you chew.

25:54.353 --> 25:55.988
And then you take another peanut

25:56.055 --> 25:58.290
and you put it in your mouth
and you chew

25:58.357 --> 25:59.859
-like a human being.
-Fritz, please, I...

25:59.926 --> 26:01.861
And then, when the camera
comes to you,

26:01.928 --> 26:04.163
people know that
you are a human being

26:04.230 --> 26:07.066
and not an acting monkey,
and you eat again,

26:07.133 --> 26:08.567
-and you eat slowly...
-Fritz, please...

26:08.635 --> 26:11.270
No, you will commit to the scene

26:11.337 --> 26:12.705
and to the character!

26:12.772 --> 26:14.607
More like an actual actress

26:14.674 --> 26:16.776
and less like
someone's girlfriend

26:16.843 --> 26:19.311
who was hired on a whim!

26:21.580 --> 26:24.150
(peanuts clattering on floor)

26:25.551 --> 26:27.687
Again.

26:29.355 --> 26:31.090
(indistinct conversations)

26:31.157 --> 26:33.726
("We Wish You
a Merry Christmas" playing)

26:33.793 --> 26:35.828
-Hey.
-Hi.

26:35.895 --> 26:38.030
Monroe, you made it.

26:38.097 --> 26:39.866
Yeah, I thought
I'd just stop by.

26:39.932 --> 26:42.068
Good. Let's go find Burt.

26:42.134 --> 26:43.402
Come on.

26:43.469 --> 26:45.705
Excuse us, guys.

26:45.772 --> 26:47.073
Well, speak of the devil.

26:47.139 --> 26:50.242
-Burt, this is...
-Monroe Stahr. -Hey.

26:50.309 --> 26:51.778
Pleasure to meet you.

26:51.844 --> 26:54.113
This is a Christmas party.

26:54.180 --> 26:57.817
I didn't know your people
celebrated Christmas, Monroe.

26:59.952 --> 27:01.487
-Gee, Burt.
-No, that's all right.

27:01.553 --> 27:04.123
That's all right, Clint.

27:05.591 --> 27:08.560
You know, I just remembered
a script that needs reading,

27:08.627 --> 27:11.330
but thanks for the offer.

27:11.397 --> 27:14.366
You have a lovely home, Burt.

27:14.433 --> 27:15.868
And merry Christmas.

27:17.904 --> 27:20.039
-(overlapping conversations)
-(music continues)

27:20.106 --> 27:22.942
BURT (singsongy):
Gordon, Judy.

27:23.009 --> 27:24.811
Welcome. Lovely to see you.

27:24.877 --> 27:28.114
Make yourselves at home.

27:36.789 --> 27:39.258
(engine starts)

27:42.328 --> 27:44.563
(engine stops)

27:44.630 --> 27:47.099
(music continues in distance)

