* Good King Wenceslas *

27:54.040 --> 27:57.744
* Last looked out
on the feast of Stephen *

27:57.810 --> 28:00.579
* When the snow lay
round about *

28:00.646 --> 28:02.448
* Deep and crisp and even *

28:02.514 --> 28:05.752
* Brightly shone
the moon that night *

28:05.818 --> 28:07.987
* Though the frost was cruel *

28:08.054 --> 28:10.957
* When a poor man
came in sight *

28:11.023 --> 28:14.827
* Gath'ring winter fuel *

28:14.894 --> 28:17.563
-* Hither, page, and stand
by me * -* Ooh, ooh, ooh *

28:17.629 --> 28:20.232
-* If thou know'st it, telling *
-* Ooh, ooh, ooh *

28:20.299 --> 28:23.135
-* Yonder peasant, who is he? *
-* Ooh, ooh, ooh *

28:23.202 --> 28:25.838
-* Where and what his
dwelling? * -* Ooh, ooh, ooh *

28:25.905 --> 28:27.673
* "Sire, he lives
a good league hence *

28:27.740 --> 28:30.777
* "Underneath the mountain *

28:30.843 --> 28:33.746
* "Right against
the forest fence *

28:33.813 --> 28:39.318
* By Saint Agnes' fountain." *

28:42.188 --> 28:45.357
LANG:
Repetition...

28:45.424 --> 28:50.262
is the only way
to make things real.

28:53.532 --> 28:57.369
Peter Lorre... "M"...

28:57.436 --> 29:01.373
his first scene,
he's supposed to whistle

29:01.440 --> 29:05.144
"In the Hall
of the Mountain King"...

29:05.211 --> 29:10.016
but he couldn't do it
without making it comic.

29:10.082 --> 29:15.321
You know how I wiped
the smile from his face?

29:15.387 --> 29:18.090
72 takes.

29:18.157 --> 29:21.427
In the end, whistling
was so painful for him,

29:21.493 --> 29:25.197
he finally knew what
kind of movie he was in

29:25.264 --> 29:29.468
and what working for me
was gonna be like.

29:29.535 --> 29:31.403
(toilet flushes)

29:31.470 --> 29:34.006
He was lucky to have you.

29:35.274 --> 29:37.176
(Kathleen sighs)

29:38.077 --> 29:41.948
(Kathleen groans)

29:42.014 --> 29:46.052
I hope we understand
each other now, Kathleen.

29:48.587 --> 29:50.589
Yes, Fritz.

29:50.656 --> 29:52.524
I understand you.

30:06.772 --> 30:08.274
What the hell is this?

30:08.340 --> 30:09.775
Ask Nathan.

30:09.842 --> 30:12.811
NATHAN:
I found him on the street.

30:12.879 --> 30:14.613
-It's our Christmas dinner.
-Max.

30:14.680 --> 30:16.348
-Is that my jacket?
-Max.

30:16.415 --> 30:17.950
-Get over there, get over there.
-Max.

30:23.455 --> 30:25.624
Hey.

30:25.691 --> 30:27.793
Hey, buddy, you got to scram.
You got to get out of here.

30:27.860 --> 30:29.195
(man shouting)

30:29.261 --> 30:31.663
-Stop!
-(Miner grunting)

30:31.730 --> 30:32.965
-Stop! Stop!
-(grunting)

30:33.032 --> 30:34.333
Oh, my God.

30:34.400 --> 30:37.569
Stop!

30:37.636 --> 30:41.073
* Adeste *

30:41.140 --> 30:45.577
* Fideles *

30:45.644 --> 30:51.150
* Laeti triumphantes *

30:51.217 --> 30:58.524
* Venite, venite... *

30:58.590 --> 31:05.031
* In Bethlehem... *

31:06.665 --> 31:09.468
* Natum *

31:09.535 --> 31:13.605
* Videte *

31:13.672 --> 31:15.607
* Regem *

31:15.674 --> 31:20.079
* Angelorum *

