* Adoremus *

31:33.692 --> 31:37.529
* Venite *

31:37.596 --> 31:42.468
* Adoremus *

31:42.534 --> 31:50.642
* Dominum. *

31:50.709 --> 31:52.644
Hey, you got a pay phone?

31:52.711 --> 31:55.681
In back.

31:55.747 --> 31:58.617
Can I pour you anything?

31:58.684 --> 32:00.752
-Club soda.
-Got it.

32:00.819 --> 32:04.023
And another round
for the loving couple, on me.

32:04.090 --> 32:06.392
Hey, merry Christmas, friend.

32:06.458 --> 32:08.194
Merry Christmas.

32:10.829 --> 32:12.464
(coins clatter, bell dings)

32:12.531 --> 32:15.201
-(clears throat)
-WOMAN: Operator.

32:15.267 --> 32:17.636
Long distance, please.

32:17.703 --> 32:18.971
Oh, Mr. Brady,

32:19.038 --> 32:21.440
I've got a Mr. Perry
on the phone from...

32:21.507 --> 32:23.709
Chicago. Right.

32:23.775 --> 32:26.212
David, what's the good word?

32:30.482 --> 32:31.617
I see.

32:32.818 --> 32:35.487
I see.

32:35.554 --> 32:37.023
Thanks.

32:37.089 --> 32:40.426
Sure. Sure,
it could turn around.

32:40.492 --> 32:42.961
Yes, merry Christmas
to you, too.

32:45.931 --> 32:47.466
(pay phone rings)

32:50.636 --> 32:51.803
Yes?

32:51.870 --> 32:53.105
OPERATOR (over phone):
I'll connect you now.

32:53.172 --> 32:56.075
All right.

32:56.142 --> 32:57.776
MRS. STERNBERG (over phone):
Milton?

32:57.843 --> 32:59.445
Hi, Ma.

32:59.511 --> 33:00.946
MRS. STERNBERG:
Is something wrong?

33:01.013 --> 33:03.382
No, no, I just wanted
to say hello

33:03.449 --> 33:06.418
and, uh, merry Christmas.

33:06.485 --> 33:08.120
(chuckles)

33:08.187 --> 33:09.755
MRS. STERNBERG:
Merry...?

33:09.821 --> 33:11.123
It's 1:00 in the morning here.

33:11.190 --> 33:12.891
I know, I know, I'm sorry.

33:12.958 --> 33:17.196
Um, I realized I hadn't asked
you about your hip in a while.

33:17.263 --> 33:20.966
You-you said you were having
a hard time walking.

33:21.033 --> 33:23.669
That was five months ago,
darling.

33:23.735 --> 33:26.338
Last time you called.

33:26.405 --> 33:29.841
I guess you're right.

33:29.908 --> 33:31.410
Is it any better?

33:31.477 --> 33:33.145
(clears throat)

33:33.212 --> 33:37.116
No, I've just learned
not to mind it.

33:38.684 --> 33:40.619
How's work?

33:40.686 --> 33:43.021
Ah, work's fine.

33:43.089 --> 33:45.991
How's everything else?

33:46.058 --> 33:49.761
Are you seeing anyone?

33:49.828 --> 33:51.563
I am, actually.

33:51.630 --> 33:53.065
A very nice girl.

33:53.132 --> 33:54.466
Before you ask...

33:54.533 --> 33:56.302
before you ask
what you're about to ask,

33:56.368 --> 33:59.538
no, she isn't,
but she can cook.

33:59.605 --> 34:01.507
Hmm, wonderful.

34:01.573 --> 34:04.776
I hope you enjoy a lifetime of
ham sandwiches with mayonnaise.

34:04.843 --> 34:07.179
(laughs)

34:07.246 --> 34:10.782
I think you'd like her.

34:10.849 --> 34:13.719
What does she call you?

34:13.784 --> 34:15.321
What, Ma?

34:15.387 --> 34:18.724
This... this girl,
does she call you Milton?

34:18.790 --> 34:21.893
Or that other name?

34:21.960 --> 34:26.331
She calls me Monroe
like everyone else out here.

34:28.199 --> 34:31.337
Then I'm not so sure
I'd like her.

34:34.773 --> 34:36.108
Darling, it's late.

34:36.175 --> 34:39.010
Yeah, I'm sorry to wake you.

34:39.077 --> 34:40.246
Good night, Milton.

34:40.312 --> 34:41.813
Yeah, night, Ma.

34:52.391 --> 34:57.163
On second thought...
I'll take an Irish whiskey.

34:57.229 --> 34:59.531
BARTENDER:
Sure thing.

35:08.907 --> 35:12.678
It's dying... everywhere.

35:14.012 --> 35:19.985
They're staying away in droves,
even in the Midwest.

35:20.051 --> 35:21.420
It's over.

35:21.487 --> 35:23.989
We needed this to be a hit.

35:24.055 --> 35:25.891
The mortgage, the house...

35:25.957 --> 35:28.560
Mayer, Christ.

35:28.627 --> 35:32.130
It had to be a hit.
It had to be.

35:32.198 --> 35:36.868
Now... it's failing.

35:39.938 --> 35:41.740
I failed.

35:41.807 --> 35:44.042
Pat.

35:44.109 --> 35:46.878
(crying): I'm afraid I'm gonna
drag you down with me.

35:46.945 --> 35:48.113
Jesus.

35:48.180 --> 35:49.481
Pat.

35:52.951 --> 35:55.854
My mother warned me about you.

35:55.921 --> 35:57.122
She did?

35:57.189 --> 35:59.458
Yup.

35:59.525 --> 36:02.127
She said you were a bad bet...

36:02.194 --> 36:05.531
because you were so sure
of yourself.

36:07.933 --> 36:10.802
"A man like that

36:10.869 --> 36:13.905
"will never need you

36:13.972 --> 36:17.476
as much as he needs success."

36:17.543 --> 36:20.279
But you didn't listen.

36:20.346 --> 36:22.180
Course not.

36:22.248 --> 36:25.217
I loved you.

36:29.788 --> 36:33.292
And I believed you'd give me
attractive children.

36:37.696 --> 36:40.799
I do need you.

36:40.866 --> 36:43.269
My Rose.

36:43.335 --> 36:45.136
Well, let me tell you something.

36:45.203 --> 36:48.039
Pat Brady's a king.

36:48.106 --> 36:52.210
Pat Brady is a giant...

36:52.278 --> 36:55.981
bigger than any one picture.

36:56.047 --> 36:59.751
He owns all this...

37:01.820 --> 37:05.857
...and I still love him.

37:11.530 --> 37:13.999
Even crying like a baby?

37:14.065 --> 37:16.234
Especially crying like a baby.

37:19.037 --> 37:21.507
(Brady sighs)

37:23.609 --> 37:26.445
I don't deserve you.

37:26.512 --> 37:28.213
BARTENDER (voice-over):
Last call.

37:28.280 --> 37:30.482
STAHR:
Last call?

37:30.549 --> 37:32.250
Well, I'm trying to leave early.

37:32.318 --> 37:33.452
Christmas and all.

37:33.519 --> 37:35.954
Oh, yeah, of course. Sorry.

37:36.021 --> 37:38.790
(Stahr clears throat)

37:38.857 --> 37:41.760
Meeting up with my girl,

37:41.827 --> 37:45.597
then we go with her family
to their place for the day.

37:45.664 --> 37:46.832
You?

37:46.898 --> 37:49.234
I don't go in much
for Christmas. Keep it.

37:49.301 --> 37:50.602
Oh. Thanks.

37:50.669 --> 37:52.103
Why not?

37:52.170 --> 37:53.605
Jewish.

37:53.672 --> 37:57.709
Hmm. Well, what do Jewish folks
do for Christmas then?

37:57.776 --> 38:00.479
Ah, hide mostly.

38:00.546 --> 38:03.982
Growing up, I used to go
to the Yiddish theater

38:04.049 --> 38:07.252
with my uncle and father.

38:07.319 --> 38:08.954
But not anymore?

38:09.020 --> 38:11.823
-Mm.
-Why not?

38:11.890 --> 38:13.825
I don't know.

38:13.892 --> 38:16.328
Guess I'm not all that
Jewish anymore.

38:16.395 --> 38:19.030
Well, then what are you?

38:19.097 --> 38:20.899
I make pictures.

38:20.966 --> 38:22.534
Oh.

38:22.601 --> 38:25.337
Didn't know that was a religion.

38:25.404 --> 38:28.239
(chuckles)
It must be.

38:28.306 --> 38:32.143
Everyone in it
is constantly praying.

38:32.210 --> 38:33.812
Hey, you ever go?

38:33.879 --> 38:35.447
To the pictures?

38:35.514 --> 38:37.182
Can't say that I do.

38:37.248 --> 38:38.617
Why not?

38:38.684 --> 38:41.787
Y'all ain't really
making them for me.

38:43.689 --> 38:46.492
What do you think
they'd look like if we did?

38:47.559 --> 38:49.861
A bit more colorful, I suppose.

38:49.928 --> 38:52.063
Oh.

38:52.130 --> 38:54.600
I really got to be closing up.

39:00.171 --> 39:03.442
You got somewhere to go?

39:04.510 --> 39:06.077
Merry Christmas.

39:06.144 --> 39:08.614
(cello playing)

39:11.483 --> 39:13.952
* *

39:18.156 --> 39:20.258
HACKETT:
Hannah. (clears throat)

39:20.325 --> 39:21.460
Hannah.

39:22.728 --> 39:25.130
Hannah!

39:25.196 --> 39:28.500
(Hackett sighs)

39:28.567 --> 39:32.471
Can you just stop for a second?

39:34.506 --> 39:38.309
It was stupid
going to that church.

39:38.376 --> 39:39.945
It was a mistake.

39:40.011 --> 39:41.980
Why?

39:42.047 --> 39:43.582
I knew all of it.

39:43.649 --> 39:48.186
The sounds, the smell,

39:48.253 --> 39:50.055
the lights from the candles

39:50.121 --> 39:52.724
and that song.

39:52.791 --> 39:56.061
So familiar, like home...

39:58.530 --> 40:00.532
...except the faces.

40:03.535 --> 40:06.004
And I can't...

40:08.173 --> 40:10.842
That's all gone.

40:23.021 --> 40:26.157
I came to this country
when I was four.

40:28.760 --> 40:30.929
We didn't know a soul.

40:34.232 --> 40:36.935
No one knew us.

40:37.002 --> 40:38.570
No one cared to know
four more wops

40:38.637 --> 40:40.572
who couldn't speak
a lick of English.

40:40.639 --> 40:44.209
After work, my dad and I

40:44.275 --> 40:48.780
would wander through Manhattan,
up and down.

40:48.847 --> 40:52.918
And then one night
we hear this laughter

40:52.984 --> 40:55.086
coming from the theater--
it was a puppet show.

40:55.153 --> 40:59.491
So we go in, we sit down,
and I'm on his lap.

40:59.558 --> 41:01.560
And everyone around us
is howling,

41:01.627 --> 41:04.362
and I look up at my father,
and he's crying.

41:04.429 --> 41:07.398
And he's crying...

41:07.465 --> 41:09.801
because he had no idea

41:09.868 --> 41:12.403
what all these people
were laughing at.

41:12.470 --> 41:14.372
These strangers.

41:14.439 --> 41:16.708
He was miserable.

41:16.775 --> 41:20.111
But we went back
the next night...

41:20.178 --> 41:21.580
and the next.

41:21.647 --> 41:24.783
And he started to understand.

41:24.850 --> 41:28.453
And after a while, so did I--
I started to get the jokes,

41:28.520 --> 41:32.490
and these people started to feel
a little less like strangers.

41:42.200 --> 41:45.003
Go ahead, keep playing.

41:45.070 --> 41:47.773
I'll shut up.

41:56.081 --> 41:59.017
* *

42:29.114 --> 42:31.549
* *

42:43.094 --> 42:46.131
-Daddy, you can't clump it all
in one spot like that. -Well...

42:46.197 --> 42:47.966
It makes the tree
look lopsided.

42:48.033 --> 42:49.467
Why don't I just
watch you do it.

42:49.534 --> 42:50.669
You take such pleasure in it.

42:50.736 --> 42:52.470
-Try again.
-She'll give you notes.

42:52.537 --> 42:54.205
(door closes)

42:54.272 --> 42:55.907
(Brady chuckles)

42:55.974 --> 42:58.710
ANNIE MAE:
You all have a visitor.

42:58.777 --> 43:00.746
Merry Christmas.

43:03.982 --> 43:06.317
Uh, I'm empty-handed, sorry.

43:06.384 --> 43:08.053
Well, merry Christmas anyway.

43:08.119 --> 43:09.655
I hope you're crashing
our party

43:09.721 --> 43:11.556
to bring me some news
about the box office.

43:11.623 --> 43:12.991
I wish I could say so.

43:13.058 --> 43:14.760
The evening numbers
any better?

43:14.826 --> 43:16.862
If we're gonna talk
about that,

43:16.928 --> 43:18.363
I'm gonna need a real drink.

43:18.429 --> 43:20.365
(phone ringing)

43:20.431 --> 43:21.366
Uh, I'll get it, Annie Mae.

43:29.207 --> 43:32.310
STAHR (chuckles):
It's, uh...

43:32.377 --> 43:34.345
it's been a long night.

43:36.247 --> 43:37.749
I don't know what
I'm doing here.

43:37.816 --> 43:39.851
I don't either.

43:41.386 --> 43:43.655
This is our family Christmas.

43:43.722 --> 43:45.256
Of course it is.

43:45.323 --> 43:47.492
-(running footsteps)
-CELIA: Mother, it's Darla.

43:47.558 --> 43:49.761
Max is in the hospital.

44:15.253 --> 44:18.223
You guys don't like candy,
do you?

44:23.862 --> 44:26.064
So what happened?

44:26.131 --> 44:29.835
It's so stupid,
I don't want to say.

44:36.107 --> 44:39.945
Nathan and me were
walking home from the movie,

44:40.011 --> 44:43.081
and we saw this hobo
lying in the street.

44:44.382 --> 44:48.553
And Nathan asked,
"What if we brought him in?

44:48.619 --> 44:50.355
"Like in the picture?

44:50.421 --> 44:53.391
Give him food and stuff?"

44:55.626 --> 44:57.963
And so we did.

44:58.029 --> 45:00.531
Brought him home, fed him,

45:00.598 --> 45:02.868
like in the movie.

45:02.934 --> 45:05.236
Let him sleep in Max's bed.

45:05.303 --> 45:07.873
Then Max came home

45:07.939 --> 45:10.408
and asked the guy to leave.

45:12.310 --> 45:14.913
The guy beat him up
pretty bad.

45:23.321 --> 45:25.256
(Stahr sighs)

45:28.593 --> 45:32.630
You know, movies are stories.

45:32.697 --> 45:35.433
Right?

45:35.500 --> 45:37.735
They're not real life.

45:39.104 --> 45:41.439
They're better than real life.

45:43.508 --> 45:46.144
CELIA:
Darla, Nathan.

45:46.211 --> 45:47.645
He's awake.

45:47.712 --> 45:49.147
And he wants to see you two.

45:49.214 --> 45:51.249
Nathan.

45:55.053 --> 45:58.723
* Silent night *

45:58.790 --> 46:03.461
* Holy night *

46:03.528 --> 46:06.731
* All is calm *

46:06.798 --> 46:10.936
* And all is bright *

46:11.002 --> 46:14.305
* Round yon virgin *

46:14.372 --> 46:16.007
STAHR:
Rose?

46:16.074 --> 46:17.708
* Mother and child *

46:17.775 --> 46:20.045
Is she okay?

46:20.111 --> 46:21.712
* Holy infant *

46:21.779 --> 46:23.815
You need some company?

46:23.882 --> 46:27.953
* So tender and mild *

46:28.019 --> 46:30.321
* Full of *

46:30.388 --> 46:38.296
* Heavenly joy *

46:38.363 --> 46:41.399
* Full of *

46:41.466 --> 46:45.270
* Heavenly *

46:45.336 --> 46:49.975
* Joy. *

46:51.642 --> 46:55.146
VAJNA: This is what
you've reduced me to.

46:55.213 --> 46:58.549
Lending my house
to a pretentious Kraut,

46:58.616 --> 47:00.518
and then breaking into it,

47:00.585 --> 47:02.553
just to see you.

47:03.989 --> 47:05.423
I guess between your new job

47:05.490 --> 47:06.824
and your new boyfriend,

47:06.892 --> 47:09.260
you're never gonna
be alone anymore.

47:09.327 --> 47:11.796
(whispering):
Rupert, they'll hear you.

47:11.863 --> 47:14.099
You can drop the accent, Jane.
It's me.

47:15.633 --> 47:18.970
I thought we weren't gonna use
that name anymore.

47:19.037 --> 47:20.906
What is wrong with you?

47:20.972 --> 47:24.375
They're right down the hall.

47:24.442 --> 47:27.612
VAJNA: I don't like chasing you,
it's demeaning.

47:27.678 --> 47:30.048
And we're partners, right?

47:30.115 --> 47:34.852
Things have gotten...
complicated.

47:34.920 --> 47:37.455
Complicated? How?

47:37.522 --> 47:39.857
Monroe.

47:39.925 --> 47:41.927
Then they're not complicated
at all.

47:41.993 --> 47:44.795
We fell in love.

47:44.862 --> 47:46.998
Uh-uh.
Monroe doesn't love you,

47:47.065 --> 47:48.499
he doesn't even know you.

47:48.566 --> 47:51.970
He's in love with a character
you're playing,

47:52.037 --> 47:53.939
the reminder of his dead wife.

47:54.005 --> 47:56.807
That's why this worked,
you're a good actress.

47:56.874 --> 47:58.609
If he loved you,

47:58.676 --> 48:01.446
you wouldn't be here on
Christmas doing circus tricks

48:01.512 --> 48:03.481
for a pig like Lang.

48:03.548 --> 48:06.384
Remember that girl
who got off the bus

48:06.451 --> 48:08.886
from Wisconsin,

48:08.954 --> 48:10.755
and I took her in.

48:10.821 --> 48:12.523
Taught her an accent,

48:12.590 --> 48:14.926
turned her into someone
Monroe would notice.

48:14.993 --> 48:18.129
And then he did.

48:18.196 --> 48:21.166
That's called management.

48:21.232 --> 48:22.900
But management isn't free.

48:22.968 --> 48:24.535
You can't simply
walk away from it

48:24.602 --> 48:26.637
just because you've become
the First Lady of Malibu.

48:26.704 --> 48:28.673
-I just wanted to work.
-And you're working.

48:28.739 --> 48:29.941
Like I promised.

48:30.008 --> 48:32.043
-It's all happening.
-Shh.

48:32.110 --> 48:33.611
Everything you told me
you wanted.

48:33.678 --> 48:35.913
-Everything we dreamed of.
-(Kathleen sighs)

48:35.981 --> 48:37.448
And more.

48:37.515 --> 48:40.118
Of course, if this is all
too much for you,

48:40.185 --> 48:42.020
we can just go, right now.

48:42.087 --> 48:44.755
I'll put you on the next bus
back to Oshkosh.

48:44.822 --> 48:48.259
-Egg Harbor.
-Same difference.

48:52.063 --> 48:54.199
Is that what you want?

48:56.934 --> 48:59.537
(quietly):
No.

48:59.604 --> 49:01.239
Then say it.

49:02.873 --> 49:05.776
It's not what I want.

49:05.843 --> 49:07.078
Say it again.

49:07.145 --> 49:10.548
-It's not what I want.
-Good.

49:10.615 --> 49:12.984
'Cause we got plans.

49:23.928 --> 49:26.064
(waves crashing in distance)

49:30.401 --> 49:32.403
* *

50:11.509 --> 50:13.444
(laughs quietly)

50:29.827 --> 50:31.596
("Winter Wonderland" plays)

50:31.662 --> 50:36.467
* Sleigh bells ring,
are you listening... *

50:36.534 --> 50:38.069
Brady here.

50:38.136 --> 50:41.038
Yeah. Merry...
happy what-have-you.

50:41.106 --> 50:42.773
Give it to me straight.

50:42.840 --> 50:44.075
* We're happy tonight *

50:44.142 --> 50:45.710
* Walking
in a winter wonderland *

50:45.776 --> 50:47.578
Christ.

50:47.645 --> 50:49.780
That's terrific.

50:49.847 --> 50:51.782
Everywhere?

50:51.849 --> 50:55.019
Great. Great.

50:55.086 --> 50:57.021
No. I had a feeling.

50:57.088 --> 50:58.756
An overnight sensation, huh?

50:58.823 --> 51:01.226
Just like "The Devil to Pay!"
back in '30.

51:01.292 --> 51:03.161
Yeah. Listen, thanks.

51:03.228 --> 51:05.296
Thanks again.

51:06.864 --> 51:08.333
Good news, Mr. Brady?

51:08.399 --> 51:10.168
* Then pretend
he is Parson Brown *

51:10.235 --> 51:12.770
They came. Last night.

51:12.837 --> 51:16.441
And today, on Christmas Day,
a little miracle.

51:16.507 --> 51:19.377
People told other people,
it's snowballing everywhere.

51:19.444 --> 51:21.879
"Word of mouth."
How about that?

51:21.946 --> 51:23.848
Hey!

51:25.082 --> 51:27.152
I just ruined
Louis Mayer's day!

51:27.218 --> 51:29.254
* The plans that we've made *

51:29.320 --> 51:32.823
* Walking
in a winter wonderland *

51:32.890 --> 51:34.759
* *

51:38.196 --> 51:41.199
Seen worse.

51:41.266 --> 51:43.401
* *

51:51.342 --> 51:54.379
Are you guys statues?

51:54.445 --> 51:55.780
Come on.

51:55.846 --> 51:58.883
Grab that broom.

51:58.949 --> 52:00.885
("Winter Wonderland" continues)

52:04.755 --> 52:06.891
(music fades)

52:11.762 --> 52:13.698
Monroe.

52:17.067 --> 52:20.538
I'm back.

52:21.872 --> 52:24.342
Wh...

52:30.215 --> 52:32.317
(kisses)

52:32.383 --> 52:34.785
I was so stupid
to send you away.

52:34.852 --> 52:37.121
(sighs)

52:37.188 --> 52:39.857
I don't want to be away
from you again.

52:39.924 --> 52:42.860
Not even for a second.

52:42.927 --> 52:44.362
KATHLEEN:
Um...

52:44.429 --> 52:48.433
I have something
I need to tell you.

52:49.066 --> 52:51.369
Sure.

52:56.641 --> 52:58.976
What is it?

52:59.043 --> 53:01.712
Um...

53:05.316 --> 53:07.918
Oh...

53:07.985 --> 53:11.155
It's been a long night.

53:11.222 --> 53:13.157
I'm tired.

53:13.224 --> 53:16.160
I'll tell you later.

53:16.227 --> 53:18.929
Marry me.

53:20.365 --> 53:21.832
It's what I want.

53:21.899 --> 53:24.469
-What?
-It's what I want for Christmas.

53:24.535 --> 53:28.138
I don't like who I am
when you're not around.

53:28.205 --> 53:31.108
Marry me.

53:31.175 --> 53:32.677
Yes?

53:32.743 --> 53:34.178
("Winter Wonderland"
resumes playing)

53:34.245 --> 53:36.146
Yes.

53:36.213 --> 53:38.115
Yes. Yes.

53:38.182 --> 53:39.484
* Later on *

53:39.550 --> 53:41.986
* We'll conspire *

53:42.052 --> 53:45.523
* As we dream by the fire *

53:45.590 --> 53:47.625
* To face unafraid *

53:47.692 --> 53:49.660
* The plans that we've made *

53:49.727 --> 53:53.331
* Walking in
a winter wonderland.*

